article.description: Loyola Marymount surged past Cal State Bakersfield in the second half for an 81-73 victory Sunday.
article.headline: Hamilton's career-best 19 points lead Lions to 6th win in row
article.linkText: Loyola Marymount surges to 6th straight victory
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Ashley Hamilton scored a career-best 19 points, LaRon Armstead added 18 and Vernon Teel had 17 as Loyola Marymount surged past Cal State Bakersfield in the second half for an 81-73 victory Sunday. The Lions (9-7) have won six straight, their longest streak since the 1995-96 season, and three straight on the road for the first time since winning their final road game in 1994-95 and the first two in 1995-96. Santwon Latunde led the Roadrunners (2-11) with 20 points and 21 rebounds. Teel finished one rebound and one assist shy of a triple-double, and Hamilton came within one rebound of a double-double. The game was tied 40-40 at halftime. Loyola Marymount opened the second half on a 10-3 run and led the rest of the way. The Lions extended their advantage to as many as 14 and didn't allow Cal State Bakersfield to get closer than five.
